  <prompt>
    Create the new `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` concrete class ŌĆö the load-bearing bridge
    between the R5 chat-driven Summarize agent-tool path (task 015 / `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool`)
    and the R5 chat-driven Summarize direct endpoint (task 014 /
    `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/summarize`). Both downstream paths MUST converge
    on a single internal method on this orchestrator; that convergence is the entire reason
    this class exists (per spec FR-01 + FR-08 + SC-08 ŌĆö "both paths produce identical output").

    The orchestrator is chat-session-scoped (operates on a `sessionId` + `fileIds` subset of
    `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]`) and composes EXISTING platform services ŌĆö it MUST NOT
    re-implement orchestration logic already provided by `AnalysisOrchestrationService` or
    `PlaybookService`. Per R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.1 the canonical orchestrators are NOT to be
    paralleled. The justification for a NEW class (rather than an extension on
    `AnalysisOrchestrationService`) is that this is a NEW kind of orchestration ŌĆö chat-session
    scope, session-files RAG index, multi-file combined-summary semantics, and chat-tool/endpoint
    convergence shape ŌĆö that the existing analysis-and-playbook orchestrator does not cover.
    This justification MUST be explicitly stated in code comments and the task notes per
    spec ┬¦"MUST cite the existing component if reusing; if proposing new, cite the gap".

    The class is a CONCRETE class with NO interface (per ADR-010 ŌĆö no genuine seam beyond
    unit-testing). It depends on existing services: `RagService` (consumed with the new
    `sessionId` filter shipped by task 002), `RagIndexingPipeline.IndexSessionFileAsync`
    (task 003), `ChatSessionManager` (extended by task 004 with `UploadedFiles[]`), the
    Summarize playbook execution path through the existing `IPlaybookService` /
    `AnalysisOrchestrationService.ExecutePlaybookAsync`, `AnalysisChunk.FieldDelta` (task 005
    additive variant), and the Structured Outputs streaming path (task 006). Registration
    lives inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` per ADR-010 feature-module pattern ŌĆö ZERO new
    top-level `Program.cs` lines and NO new feature flag (per R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.2 + ┬¦3.3).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer fluent in Minimal-API BFF orchestration, IAsyncEnumerable streaming
    over SSE, Azure OpenAI Structured Outputs incremental JSON, and Spaarke's existing
    `AnalysisOrchestrationService` + `IPlaybookService` composition pattern. Familiar with
    ADR-010 (DI minimalism, concrete classes), ADR-013 (BFF-only AI; agents via factory),
    ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline, and R5's reuse mandate per project CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.1.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new concrete class `Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Chat.SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`
    (file: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs`)
    that exposes ONE internal/public streaming entry point (e.g.
    `IAsyncEnumerable&lt;AnalysisStreamChunk&gt; SummarizeSessionFilesAsync(SessionSummarizeRequest, CancellationToken)`)
    consumed by BOTH task 014's direct endpoint AND task 015's agent-tool handler. The class
    composes existing platform services (NO new orchestrator built; NO new playbook engine;
    NO new chat agent). Registered inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` (Analysis-services
    feature module). Unit tests verify: (a) the single convergence method exists and is the
    single delegation target for both paths; (b) playbook execution delegates to existing
    `IPlaybookService` / `AnalysisOrchestrationService`; (c) session-scoped RAG retrieval
    delegates to existing `RagService` with `RagSearchOptions.SessionId` set; (d)
    multi-file combined-summary deterministic interjection emits before streaming starts;
    (e) decline-to-find path streams the structured decline response. Acceptance criteria
    below are all green; `code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass; BFF publish-size
    delta reported.
  </goal>

