  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.1 (reuse mandate)">MUST NOT introduce a parallel orchestrator to `AnalysisOrchestrationService` or `InsightsOrchestrator`. This new class is justified ONLY because chat-session-scoped Summarize orchestration is a NEW kind of orchestration not covered by existing services. Justification MUST be explicitly written in the class XML doc-comment AND in task notes per project CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.1 step 3 ("if proposing new component: cite the gap explicitly").</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.1 (reuse mandate)">MUST reuse: `RagService.SearchAsync()` (with `RagSearchOptions.SessionId` per task 002) for grounded retrieval; `RagIndexingPipeline.IndexSessionFileAsync` (task 003) when staging files into the session-files index if needed at orchestration time; `IPlaybookService` + `AnalysisOrchestrationService.ExecutePlaybookAsync` for actual Summarize-playbook execution; `ChatSessionManager` (extended by task 004) for reading `UploadedFiles[]`; `AnalysisChunk` (with `FieldDelta` variant from task 005) as the SSE envelope; Structured-Outputs streaming path from task 006.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010 (DI minimalism + concrete classes)">Class MUST be CONCRETE ŌĆö NO interface unless a genuine seam exists. Unit-testing alone is NOT a genuine seam per ADR-010. The acceptance criterion "no interface introduced" is testable by grep. `virtual` methods only if Null-Object subclassing required ŌĆö NOT expected per R5 ┬¦3.2.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010 + R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.3 (DI discipline)">Registration MUST be inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` via the existing `AddAnalysisOrchestrationServices(...)` helper (or a new private helper inside the module) ŌĆö ZERO new `services.AddXxx()` lines added to `Program.cs`. Lifetime: `Scoped` (matches `AnalysisOrchestrationService` and Insights orchestration pattern).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018 (Flag Scope Discipline) + R5 ┬¦3.2">MUST NOT add any new feature flag. Kill-switch coverage inherits from existing `Analysis:Enabled` (parent gate of `AnalysisServicesModule.AddAnalysisOrchestrationServices`) and `Chat:Enabled`. ADR-032 Null-Object NOT applicable ŌĆö orchestrator is registered only when the parent compound-AI-ON branch is active; consumers (endpoint task 014 + tool handler task 015) inherit the same gating.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013 (AI architecture ŌĆö BFF-only)">Class lives in BFF (`Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Chat` namespace). Agent-tool consumer (task 015) goes through `SprkChatAgentFactory` per ADR-013; this orchestrator is the BFF-side delegation target ŌĆö NOT a chat-agent itself.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-01 + FR-08 + SC-08 (convergence ŌĆö load-bearing)">A SINGLE internal/public method MUST be the convergence point. Task 014 (direct endpoint) AND task 015 (agent-tool handler) MUST both delegate to that exact method with identical request semantics. Output `DocumentAnalysisResult` shape MUST match between paths. This is the load-bearing reason this class exists; absence of single-method convergence = task failure.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-04 (combined-summary interjection)">For multi-file (`fileIds.Count >= 2`) requests, the orchestrator MUST emit a deterministic chat-layer interjection ("I'll provide a combined summary for the files you uploaded") via `AnalysisChunk` (Type = "text" or equivalent) BEFORE the playbook streams. Single-file requests MUST NOT emit this.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-11 (decline-to-find structured response)">When content is insufficient, MUST chain through `DeclineToFindNode` per existing D-04 honesty contract and stream the structured `DeclineResponse` envelope ŌĆö NOT a hallucinated summary.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014 (tenant isolation)">All `RagService.SearchAsync` calls inside the orchestrator MUST set both `tenantId` AND `sessionId` filters per ADR-014 + spec NFR-03.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-007 (SpeFileStore facade)">Any file operations (if needed inside the orchestrator) MUST go via `SpeFileStore` / `DocumentCheckoutService`. The orchestrator likely does NOT perform file IO directly ŌĆö it delegates to the indexing pipeline (already done at upload time) and the playbook service.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028 (Spaarke Auth v2)">No token snapshots. Orchestrator accepts `HttpContext` (or already-resolved auth identity) per request ŌĆö does NOT cache tokens between requests.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 + CLAUDE.md ┬¦10 (BFF publish-size verification)">Per-task MANDATORY: run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; measure compressed output; report absolute size + delta in task notes / PR description; ceiling Ōēż60 MB compressed; budget R5 Ōēż+1 MB total; Ōēź+5 MB single-task delta ŌåÆ escalation.</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md (binding governance)">Placement Justification MUST be authored: this orchestrator BELONGS IN BFF (BFF-only architecture per ADR-013; chat orchestration is core BFF responsibility; no extraction candidate). State this explicitly in PR description.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md ┬¦10 F.1 (asymmetric-registration check)">Endpoint that maps unconditionally (task 014) MUST have unconditional service registration. R5 ┬¦3.2 ŌĆö R5 services unconditionally registered when `Analysis:Enabled = true` (default). Confirm registration is NOT inside a R5-specific `if (flag)` block.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md ┬¦10 (test update obligation per F-22 / D-05)">PR modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST add/update tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/`. Tests MUST cover the convergence-method contract, multi-file interjection emission, decline path, and `RagSearchOptions.SessionId` propagation.</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02 (per-session cap)">Hard cap 20 files per session ŌĆö orchestrator MUST reject `fileIds` lists &gt; 20 (or otherwise inheriting from `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]`'s upstream cap from task 004).</constraint>
  </constraints>

