    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Chat-tool Ōåö orchestrator delegation (canonical Insights mirror)" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/AssistantToolCallHandler.cs">
        Insights' Wave-E3 `AssistantToolCallHandler` is the pattern R5 mirrors for chat-tool
        delegation. AssistantToolCallHandler exposes a single async method (`HandleAsync`)
        that the BFF facade (`IInsightsAi.AssistantQueryAsync`) AND the chat-agent tool
        (`insights.query`) both delegate to. The Spaarke Assistant tool-call contract
        document binds the convergence shape. R5's `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` follows
        the same convergence pattern but for the Summarize-playbook + session-scoped RAG
        composition instead of intent classifier + playbook + RAG.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Orchestrator constructor composition + ADR-010 reduction" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs">
        `AnalysisOrchestrationService` was reduced from 21 to 10 constructor parameters by
        extracting `AnalysisDocumentLoader`, `AnalysisRagProcessor`, `AnalysisResultPersistence`.
        R5's `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` SHOULD keep its constructor lean (target Ōēż8 deps):
        likely `ChatSessionManager`, `IPlaybookService` (or `IAnalysisOrchestrationService`
        for playbook execution delegation), `RagService`, `RagIndexingPipeline`, `AiTelemetry`,
        `ILogger&lt;SessionSummarizeOrchestrator&gt;`. If composition grows, extract helpers
        like `SessionContextBuilder` rather than fattening the constructor.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="IAsyncEnumerable streaming + AnalysisChunk envelope" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs">
        Canonical streaming method shape: `public async IAsyncEnumerable&lt;AnalysisStreamChunk&gt;
        SummarizeSessionFilesAsync(SessionSummarizeRequest request, HttpContext httpContext,
        [EnumeratorCancellation] CancellationToken cancellationToken)`. Yield chunks via
        `yield return`; emit `FieldDelta` chunks during playbook stream; emit interjection
        chunk for multi-file BEFORE playbook starts; propagate `DeclineToFindNode` output
        as structured chunks unchanged.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="DI registration inside feature module" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs">
        `AddAnalysisOrchestrationServices(services, configuration)` is the existing internal
        helper. Add R5 service registration inside this helper (or a new sibling helper
        `AddR5SessionSummarizeServices(services)` called from the existing top-level if-block
        when both `documentIntelligenceEnabled` AND `analysisEnabled` are true). Lifetime:
        `Scoped`. ZERO new `services.AddXxx()` lines in `Program.cs`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Concrete-class-no-interface (ADR-010)" location=".claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md">
        ADR-010 mandates concrete classes by default. Introduce an interface ONLY when a
        genuine seam exists (Null-Object alternative needed; multiple implementations
        legitimately required; cross-module boundary). Unit-testability alone is NOT a
        seam ŌĆö test the concrete class directly with composed real or fake dependencies.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The R5 vertical slice ships a "Summarize a Document" chat-driven flow with two valid
      entry points: explicit slash command (`/summarize`) routed through a direct
      endpoint (task 014) AND natural-language invocation routed through an LLM tool-call
      to the agent tool (task 015). Spec FR-01 + FR-08 + SC-08 require IDENTICAL output
      shape from both paths. The canonical way to guarantee identity in Spaarke (per the
      Insights `AssistantToolCallHandler` pattern shipped in r2 Wave E3) is a single
      internal method on a single orchestrator that both paths delegate to. This task
      ships that orchestrator. Without it, the two paths would inevitably drift in
      streaming shape, multi-file interjection emission, decline-handling, RAG-scope
      filtering, telemetry, or output schema.
    </background>
