    <step order="3" name="Author Placement Justification + Why-New-Class Justification">
      **Mandatory step per spec + R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.1.** Before coding, author two artifacts:
      (a) **Placement Justification** (for PR description per CLAUDE.md ┬¦10): why this
      class belongs in BFF (`Services/Ai/Chat/`) ŌĆö ADR-013 BFF-only architecture; chat
      orchestration is core BFF responsibility; no extraction candidate; consumed only by
      BFF endpoint + BFF-registered chat-tool. (b) **Why-New-Class Justification** (for
      class XML doc-comment AND task notes per R5 CLAUDE.md ┬¦3.1 step 3): why a NEW class
      and not an extension of `AnalysisOrchestrationService` ŌĆö because (i) chat-session-scope
      is a NEW orchestration shape (session-files index, `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]`
      manifest); (ii) multi-file combined-summary interjection is chat-layer logic, not
      analysis-layer logic; (iii) agent-tool/endpoint convergence shape requires a dedicated
      delegation target; (iv) `AnalysisOrchestrationService` orchestrates document-record-scoped
      analysis, not chat-session-scoped synthesis. Cite spec FR-01 + FR-08 + SC-08 as the
      load-bearing convergence requirement. Save both as `notes/task-012-justifications.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Design `SessionSummarizeRequest` Input Shape">
      Define the request record/class (likely `internal sealed record SessionSummarizeRequest`)
      that captures the convergence input: `string SessionId`, `IReadOnlyList&lt;string&gt; FileIds`
      (optional ŌĆö if empty/null, defaults to ALL active `UploadedFiles[]` per spec FR-08),
      `string? StyleHint` (per agent-tool function params), `Guid? CorrelationId` (for
      `x-correlation-id` propagation per NFR-17). Both task 014 (endpoint) and task 015
      (agent tool) MUST be able to construct this same request shape.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Implement Concrete `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs`.
      Class signature: `public sealed class SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (concrete; NO
      interface; `sealed` per Insights `AssistantToolCallHandler` precedent). Constructor
      injects: `ChatSessionManager` (read `UploadedFiles[]`), `IPlaybookService` or
      `IAnalysisOrchestrationService` (delegate playbook execution to existing service ŌĆö
      pick whichever current public method shape best fits; do NOT introduce a new playbook
      orchestrator), `RagService` (session-scoped RAG retrieval for combined-summary
      grounding), `AiTelemetry`, `ILogger&lt;SessionSummarizeOrchestrator&gt;`. Target Ōēż7
      constructor params.

      Implement the SINGLE convergence method:
      ```
      public async IAsyncEnumerable&lt;AnalysisStreamChunk&gt; SummarizeSessionFilesAsync(
          SessionSummarizeRequest request,
          HttpContext httpContext,
          [EnumeratorCancellation] CancellationToken cancellationToken)
      ```
      Flow (high level ŌĆö verify against existing canonical patterns):
      1. Validate `request.SessionId` + cap `FileIds.Count` Ōēż 20 (NFR-02).
      2. Load `ChatSession` via `ChatSessionManager`; if `FileIds` empty, default to
         `chatSession.UploadedFiles[*].FileId`.
      3. If `FileIds.Count >= 2`, yield deterministic combined-summary interjection chunk
         (FR-04).
      4. Build playbook-execute request referencing task 011 playbook config + task 010
         action seed. Set `tenantId` + `sessionId` per ADR-014 / NFR-03.
      5. Delegate to existing playbook execution path (`AnalysisOrchestrationService.ExecutePlaybookAsync`
         or `IPlaybookService.ExecuteAsync` ŌĆö pick the existing canonical method;
         emphatically NOT a new method on this orchestrator).
      6. Forward each `AnalysisStreamChunk` (including `FieldDelta` variants from task 005)
         to caller via `yield return`.
      7. On `DeclineToFindNode` activation, forward the structured decline envelope unchanged
         (FR-11; do NOT post-process).
      8. Emit telemetry: `r5.summarize.invocation` event with `path = invoking-method` ŌĆö
         actually set by callers (endpoint = `direct_endpoint`; tool = `agent_tool`) via
         a `request.Path` discriminator or `ActivitySource` tag. Per spec D1-08 / NFR-12.
      Include XML doc-comments on the class + the convergence method citing the "why-new-class"
      justification + the convergence requirement (FR-01 + FR-08 + SC-08).
    </step>
